{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "Work out your brain by struggling to learn a new language.", "abstract": "Op-Ed article by author William Alexander relates his struggle to learn French, noting that it is extremely difficult for an adult to absorb a new language; suggests that effort is certainly worthwhile, even if one falls short of proficiency, because language-learning is an excellent way to exercise regions of the brain that decline with age; notes that his score on a general cognitive test improved radically after a year of French study.", "section_name": "Opinion", "print_page": "23", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [{"firstname": "William", "role": "reported", "lastname": "ALEXANDER", "rank": 1, "organization": ""}], "original": "By WILLIAM ALEXANDER", "contributor": ""}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2014/07/16/opinion/16alexander.html", "lead_paragraph": "Work out your brain by struggling to learn a new language.", "headline": {"main": "The Benefits of Failing at French", "print_headline": "The Benefits of Failing at French", "content_kicker": "Op-Ed Contributor", "kicker": "Op-Ed Contributor"}, "_id": "53c5b19838f0d844fb7d8273", "word_count": "903", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2014/07/16/opinion/0716OPEDlogan/0716OPEDlogan-thumbWide.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2014/07/16/opinion/0716OPEDlogan/0716OPEDlogan-thumbWide.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 688, "url": "images/2014/07/16/opinion/0716OPEDlogan/0716OPEDlogan-articleLarge.jpg", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2014/07/16/opinion/0716OPEDlogan/0716OPEDlogan-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": "600", "xlargeheight": "688"}, "subtype": "xlarge", "width": 600, "type": "image"}, {"height": 75, "url": "images/2014/07/16/opinion/0716OPEDlogan/0716OPEDlogan-thumbStandard.jpg", "legacy": {"thumbnail": "images/2014/07/16/opinion/0716OPEDlogan/0716OPEDlogan-thumbStandard.jpg", "thumbnailwid